results.description:
A coding dojo is a meeting where a bunch of coders get together and work on a code kata, a programming challenge to improve their skills. They code, learn and have fun away from interruptions, distractions, deadlines and production bugs. A coding dojo provides a safe environment to discuss topics like design, functional programming, testing, refactoring, choice of code editors, tools, etc.

The kata will be announced at the beginning of the dojo.

Further instructions

Bring your own laptop with a Scala IDE (Eclipse, IntelliJ, etc.) already installed and configured.

Have SBT installed on your machine.

For a quick-setup, clone this repository and follow the instructions there: https://github.com/scala-vienna/dojo-quickstart
results.name: Scala Coding Dojo

results.description:
Our fellow software craftsmen & craftswomen are organizing a Coderetreat Day here in Vienna: "Since we started with the first Global Day of Coderetreat in 2011 Vienna already has a vivid crowd of software craftsmen, which is key for great companies and products, fit for the future. Software craftsmanship is the missing link many of us often even miss in so called Agile projects."

Full details here:
http://coderetreat.org/events/global-day-of-coderetreat-vienna-2014

Please note that registration is via Eventbrite!
http://www.eventbrite.de/e/global-day-of-coderetreat-2013-vienna-tickets-9143106277

You can also RSVP here to let other fellow Scala Types that you will be there! ;-)
results.name: Global Day of Coderetreat 2013

results.description:
Based on the initiative of Roman from the Laravel User Group we invite you to the

*** DEV * XMAS * GATHERING ***

The year is coming to its end, so it is high time for a party together with other user groups from Vienna:
• Laravel, viennaPHP, viennaJS, Web Performance, Perl, System Architects, Django, ViennaDB, Symfony, Vienna Scala, ...
• So lots of people from related areas :)

AGENDA
• Opening 19:00 h.
• Having fun, discussions, drinking, eating, meeting great people
• End 23:00 h.

WHAT YOU HAVE TO DO:
• Make a reservation here or at viennaPHP.
• Bring in something to drink (water, juice, lemonade, hot red wine) and some food (bread, salads, nuts, fruits, biscuits, cakes) for a community buffet (please make a post).
• Bring you own mug, if you want to drink some hot red wine.
• Enjoy the event!

WE NEED HELP:
• Who will be so kind, to help us preparing our event space (start 17:00) and clean it up after the party?
• Who has a hot wine cooker?
• Who can bring in plastic plates, cutleries, paper cups, napkins, garbage bags?

Please contact Stefan or post here below a comment.

SPONSORS:
We already have some great sponsors for this event:
• StockWerk will offer us this awesome event space (thanks Alexander)
• M-Software will support us and give us one hot wine cooker
results.name: *** DEV * XMAS * GATHERING ***
